# Generated metadata files (regenerated by `levels recover-metadata`).
# Marked linguist-generated so GitHub folds them in PRs and drops them from
# language stats.
#
# reaches.json (geometry), reaches-gradient.json (gradient_profile samples), and
# huc_name.csv (the HUC6+HUC8 WBD lookup) are also -diff: a textual diff is never
# useful, so git shows "Binary files differ" instead of thousands of lines.
# reach.csv is NOT -diff — with geom + gradient_profile held out to the JSON
# sidecars (review-3 R6.1), it's the ~37 hand-edited reach-metadata columns
# (description, notes,
# optimal_flow, …) that a reviewer should still be able to read in `git diff`.
data/db/reaches.json           -diff linguist-generated
data/db/reaches-gradient.json  -diff linguist-generated
data/db/reach.csv                    linguist-generated
data/db/huc_name.csv           -diff linguist-generated
